messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path
- /cms/user/register

All HTTP methods acceptable?
- no

HTTP methods accepted (based on the code)
- HEAD: no
- POST: yes
- OPTIONS: no
- TRACE: no
- GET: no
- PUT: no
- DELETE: no
- PATCH: no

Explanation
- The app registers a blueprint with url_prefix "/cms" in app/__init__.py (register_blueprints -> create_cms registered at "/cms").
- In app/api/cms/__init__.py the cms blueprint registers the user blueprint (user_api) at url_prefix "/user".
- In app/api/cms/user.py the register endpoint is defined as @user_api.route("/register", methods=["POST"]). Combining the prefixes gives the final path /cms + /user + /register => /cms/user/register.
- The route decorator explicitly lists methods=["POST"], so only POST is accepted according to the source code. The decision about other methods is made strictly from the code (no assumptions about framework implicit behaviors), therefore HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE and PATCH are marked as not accepted.
